35. Write a PHP script using an array that checks if a string contains another string and displays the result.
<?php
$haystack = "Hello, welcome to PHP world!";
$needle = "PHP";
// check if $needle is inside $haystack
if (strpos($haystack, $needle) !== false) {
    echo "The string contains '$needle'.";
} else {
    echo "The string does not contain '$needle'.";
}
?>
Output:
The string contains 'PHP'.
